ine 120:     one ``{status: ..., supersedes_id: ...}`` from the inner attribution\n\n  Line 122:     iteration order and the second one's ``supersedes_id`` taking\n\n  Line 133:     on the fields the inner branch sets (``status``, ``supersedes_id``)\n\n  Line 136:     in ``test_contradiction_direction_invariance.py``: both the\n\n  Line 137:     canonical iteration's ``supersedes_id`` chain link AND the flipped\n\n  Line 152: async def detect_contradictions_async(\n\n  Line 161:     \"\"\"Post-commit contradiction detection — runs independently.\n\n  Line 187:         # EMBEDDED handlers fire ``detect_contradictions_async`` for\n\n  Line 204:         contradictions = await _detect(new_memory, embedding, tenant_config)\n\n  Line 205:         n_conflicts = len(contradictions) if contradictions else 0\n\n  Line 207:         if contradictions:\n\n  Line 209:                 \"Async contradiction detection found %d conflict(s) for memory %s\",\n\n  Line 210:                 len(contradictions),\n\n  Line 214:         logger.exception(\"Async contradiction detection failed for memory %s\", memory_id)\n\n  Line 232: async def detect_contradictions(\n\n  Line 238:     \"\"\"In-session contradiction detection (caller manages commit).\n\n  Line 241:     prefer detect_contradictions_async which runs post-commit.\n\n  Line 255:             \"supersedes_id\": str(new_memory.supersedes_id) if new_memory.supersedes_id else None,\n\n  Line 277:     2. Semantic conflict: high vector similarity, LLM confirms contradiction\n\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 324 matches (224 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":324,"truncated":true},"title":"supersedes_id|status = 'conflicted'|contradiction|superseded_by|supersessors","time":{"start":1780729388405,"end":1780729388434}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d639ab5cde6a1d5016a23c62c55748191af7e41b7810b066f"}},"id":"prt_e9bbe1d70001qqv30sQGoOIFCW","sessionID":"ses_164436567ffeteXLf4I1Mx29cA"